16/06/2003
WASHINGTON, USA -- Turkish Foreign Ministry Undersecretary Ugur Ziyal arrived in Washington on Monday (16 June) to exchange views with high-ranking US officials on bilateral relations. 
This is the first high-level official contact between Turkey and the United States since the war in Iraq. 
While in Washington, Ziyal will meet US State Department Undersecretary Marc Grossman and the president's deputy adviser for national security, Stephen Hadley. 
(Anadolu Agency, NTV - 16/06/03; AFP - 15/06/03)
